# DATABASE_URL is what the running app connects as - MUST be the
# least-privilege zaroda_app role (see prisma/create-app-role.sql), never
# the database owner. On Neon (and likely other managed Postgres), the
# owner role has BYPASSRLS, which makes every RLS policy in prisma/rls.sql
# silently do nothing if the app connects as the owner - see prisma/README.md.
#
# connect_timeout=30 and pool_timeout=30: Prisma's own defaults are 5s and
# 10s respectively, which a Phase 3 load test caught being too short
# against Neon specifically - a free-tier compute waking from autosuspend
# was directly observed taking 12-16s to accept its first connection
# after being idle. These are two DIFFERENT timeouts that both need
# raising: connect_timeout bounds the TCP+TLS+auth handshake itself;
# pool_timeout (separate, easy to miss) bounds how long Prisma's client
# waits for a connection from its own internal pool, and is what actually
# produces the misleading "Timed out fetching a new connection from the
# connection pool" error if left at its 10s default while the real
# connect is taking 12-16s. Neither is the same as the interactive-
# transaction timeout in TenantScopedPrismaService.run() (a separate 15s
# override already applied there and in AuthService.pinLogin). Harmless
# to leave in against an always-warm Postgres instance.
#
# connection_limit=10: left at Prisma's implicit default (num_cpus*2+1)
# this is small and un-obvious, and every interactive transaction (every
# write path in this app goes through one - see
# TenantScopedPrismaService.run()) holds a pool connection for its full
# duration. Under concurrent writes this can exhaust the pool and fail
# new requests with "Unable to start a transaction in the given time"
# rather than queuing them - caught by the same Phase 3 load test.
# 10 is sized for this pilot's stated scale (<10 terminals per DESIGN.md)
# with headroom; raise it (and Neon's own per-role connection limit) if
# the target scale grows.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://zaroda_app:password@localhost:5432/zaroda_pos?schema=public&connect_timeout=30&pool_timeout=30&connection_limit=10"
# DIRECT_URL is used only by `prisma migrate`/`prisma db execute` - the
# owner/admin role, since migrations need to create tables and roles. If
# using a pooled connection (e.g. Neon's pgbouncer endpoint, "-pooler" in
# the hostname), this should be the unpooled variant.
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/zaroda_pos?schema=public&connect_timeout=30&pool_timeout=30"
JWT_SECRET="change-me-in-every-environment"
JWT_EXPIRES_IN="8h"
# A SEPARATE secret from JWT_SECRET, deliberately - PlatformAdminJwtStrategy
# signs/verifies with this one, never JWT_SECRET, so a tenant token and a
# platform-admin token can never validate against each other's guard even
# if the two secrets were somehow confused. Shorter default expiry (4h vs
# 8h) since this identity can see every tenant.
PLATFORM_ADMIN_JWT_SECRET="change-me-in-every-environment-too-and-make-it-different-from-jwt-secret"
PLATFORM_ADMIN_JWT_EXPIRES_IN="4h"
PORT=3001
# Comma-separated allowlist of origins the terminal PWA/back-office are
# served from (browser fetch() is blocked without this - see main.ts).
# Unset allows any origin, which is fine for local dev only.
# CORS_ORIGIN="http://localhost:3002,https://pos.example.com"

# M-Pesa (Safaricom Daraja) - only needed once STK push is wired into a
# sale-completion flow (not yet - see payments/mpesa-payment.processor.ts).
# Get sandbox credentials free at developer.safaricom.co.ke.
# MPESA_CONSUMER_KEY=
# MPESA_CONSUMER_SECRET=
# MPESA_SHORTCODE=
# MPESA_PASSKEY=
# MPESA_CALLBACK_URL=
# MPESA_ENV=sandbox

# Africa's Talking SMS (see notifications/africas-talking-sms.provider.ts) -
# not yet live-tested, same "interface and call site are real, credentials
# are the deferred piece" situation as M-Pesa above. Get sandbox credentials
# free at account.africastalking.com. A missing key/username does NOT break
# anything that uses this - sends just silently report {sent: false} and
# callers (e.g. public-booking/) degrade gracefully.
# AFRICAS_TALKING_API_KEY=
# AFRICAS_TALKING_USERNAME=
# AFRICAS_TALKING_ENV=sandbox

# Base URL of the customer-facing booking pages (apps/backoffice's
# app/book/... routes) - used to build the manage-booking link texted to a
# customer after a public salon booking (public-booking/). Unset simply
# skips sending that SMS (booking creation itself is unaffected either way).
# PUBLIC_BOOKING_BASE_URL="http://localhost:3003"
